18 Section 2. KRS 160.350 is amended to read as follows:
19 (1) After considering the recommendations of a screening committee, as provided in
20 KRS 160.352, each board of education shall appoint a superintendent of schools
21 whose term of office shall begin on July 1, following the individual's appointment.
22 The appointment may be for a term of no more than four (4) years. In the event a
23 vacancy occurs in the office of superintendent prior to the expiration of the term set
24 by the board, the term shall expire on the date the vacancy occurs. Therefore, the
25 board may appoint a superintendent for a new term as provided in this subsection,
26 which shall begin on the date of the superintendent's appointment, except when the
27 vacancy occurs after a school board election and before the newly elected members
Page 3 of 21
SB000220.100 - 941 - XXXX 3/20/2026 10:05 AM Engrossed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 2/EN
1 take office. When a vacancy occurs during this period, the position shall not be
2 filled until the new members take office, but the board may appoint an acting
3 superintendent to serve a term not to exceed six (6) months. This appointment may
4 be renewed once for a period not to exceed three (3) months. If a vacancy occurs, a
5 local board may also appoint an acting superintendent during the period the
6 screening committee pursuant to KRS 160.352 conducts its business and prior to
7 the actual appointment of the new superintendent. No superintendent shall resign
8 during a term and accept a new term from the same board of education prior to the
9 expiration date of the present term. In the case of a vacancy in the office for an
10 unexpired term, the board of education shall make the appointment so that the term
11 will end on June 30. The board shall set the salary of the superintendent to be paid
12 in regular installments.
13 (2) Each board of education shall publish on the district's website and submit to the
14 Kentucky Department of Education, within thirty (30) days of execution, each
15 superintendent's contract, amendment, renewal, extension, or addendum thereto
16 as:
17 (a) A scanned copy of the fully executed document; and
18 (b) An electronic text version of the document in a format prescribed by the
19 department that accurately sets forth the terms of the executed document
20 and is accessible for publication in compliance with applicable accessibility
21 requirements.
22 (3) The department shall publish the documents submitted under subsection (2) of
23 this section within thirty (30) days of receipt on the department's website. The
24 department shall not remove information submitted under subsection (2) of this
25 section from its website for at least ten (10) school years.
26 (4) An individual shall not assume the duties of superintendent in a district until he or
27 she provides the board of education with a copy of a certificate for school
Page 4 of 21
SB000220.100 - 941 - XXXX 3/20/2026 10:05 AM Engrossed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 2/EN
1 superintendent issued by the Education Professional Standards Board or its legal
2 predecessor. A superintendent shall hold a valid certificate throughout the period of
3 employment. A superintendent shall successfully complete the training program and
4 assessment center process within two (2) years of assuming the duties of
5 superintendent. A superintendent shall not serve as director or officer of a bank,
6 trust company, or savings or loan association that has the school district's funds on
7 deposit. Following appointment, the superintendent shall establish residency in
8 Kentucky.
9 (5)[(3)] A superintendent of schools may be removed for cause by a vote of four-fifths
10 (4/5) of the membership of a board of education and upon approval by the
11 commissioner of education. However, if the dismissal of the superintendent has
12 been recommended by a highly skilled certified educator pursuant to KRS 158.6455
13 and the action is approved by the commissioner of education, the board shall
14 terminate the superintendent's contract. Written notice setting out the charges for
15 removal shall be spread on the minutes of the board and given to the
16 superintendent. The board shall seek approval by the commissioner of education for
17 removing the superintendent. The commissioner of education shall investigate the
18 accuracy of the charges made, evaluate the superintendent's overall performance
19 during the superintendent's appointment, and consider the educational performance
20 of the students in the district. Within thirty (30) days of notification, the
21 commissioner of education shall either approve or reject the board's request.
22 (6)[(4)] After the completion of a superintendent's first contract or after four (4) years,
23 whichever comes last, the board of education may, no later than June 30, extend the
24 contract of the superintendent for one (1) additional year beyond the current term of
25 employment.
