4 (c) "Level" means elementary, middle, or high school;
5 (d) "Turnaround" means a comprehensive transformation of a school to achieve
6 accelerated, meaningful, and sustainable increases in student achievement
7 through improved school leadership and school district support;
8 (e) "Turnaround plan" means a mandatory school plan that is designed to
9 improve student learning and performance with evidence-based interventions
10 as defined in ESSA and that is developed and implemented by the local
11 school district in partnership with stakeholders, including the principal, other
12 school leaders, teachers, and parents; and
13 (f) "Turnaround team" means the turnaround training and support team described
