15 (2) (a) The department shall annually identify a school for targeted support and
16 improvement if the school has one (1) or more of the same subgroups, as
17 defined by ESSA, whose performance in the state accountability system by
18 level is at or below that of all students in any of the lowest-performing five
19 percent (5%) of all schools for three (3) consecutive years.
20 (b) Beginning with the 2021-2022 school year, and every three (3) years
21 thereafter, the department shall identify a school for additional targeted
22 support and improvement if the school has one (1) or more subgroups, as
23 defined by ESSA, whose performance in the state accountability system by
24 level is at or below the summative performance of all students in any of the
25 lowest-performing five percent (5%) of all schools identified under subsection
