15 agency designated by the state board to manage interscholastic athletics, any
16 student who transfers enrollment from a district of residence to a nonresident
17 district under KRS 157.350(4)(a)[(b)] after enrolling in grade nine (9) and
18 participating in a varsity sport shall be ineligible to participate in
19 interscholastic athletics for one (1) calendar year from the date of the transfer.
20 The state board or any agency designated by the state board to manage
21 interscholastic athletics may adopt rules, policies, and bylaws and promulgate
22 administrative regulations necessary to carry out this paragraph.
23 (j) No member school shall grant a student-athlete the right to use the member
24 school's property, or intellectual property, such as trademarks, school
25 uniforms, and copyrights, in the student's earning of compensation through
26 name, image, and likeness activities. No student-athlete shall use school
27 property or such intellectual property in earning compensation through name,
