4 (3) (a) The Kentucky Board of Education is hereby authorized to lease from the State
5 Property and Buildings Commission or others, whether public or private, any
6 lands, buildings, structures, installations, and facilities suitable for use in
7 establishing and furthering television and related facilities as an aid or
8 supplement to classroom instruction throughout the Commonwealth and for
9 incidental use in any other proper public functions. The lease may be for any
10 initial term commencing with the date of the lease and ending with the next
11 ensuing June 30, which is the close of the then-current fiscal biennium of the
12 Commonwealth, with exclusive options in favor of the board to renew the
13 same for successive ensuing bienniums, July 1 in each even year to June 30 in
14 the next ensuing even year; and the rentals may be fixed at the sums in each
15 biennium, if renewed, sufficient to enable the State Property and Buildings
16 Commission to pay therefrom the maturing principal of and interest on, and
17 provide reserves for, any revenue bonds which the State Property and
18 Buildings Commission may determine to be necessary and sufficient, in
19 agreement with the board, to provide the cost of acquiring the television and
20 related facilities with appurtenances and costs as may be incident to the
21 issuance of the bonds.
22 (b) Each option of the Kentucky Board of Education to renew the lease for a
23 succeeding biennial term may be exercised at any time after the adjournment
24 of the session of the General Assembly at which appropriations shall have
25 been made for the operation of the state government for such succeeding
26 biennial term, by notifying the State Property and Buildings Commission in
27 writing, signed by the chief state school officer, and delivered to the secretary
Page 19 of 21
SB000220.100 - 941 - XXXX 3/20/2026 10:05 AM Engrossed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 2/EN
1 of the Finance and Administration Cabinet as a member of the commission.
2 The option shall be deemed automatically exercised, and the lease
3 automatically renewed for the succeeding biennium, effective on the first day
4 thereof, unless a written notice of the board's election not to renew shall have
5 been delivered in the office of the secretary of the Finance and Administration
6 Cabinet before the close of business on the last working day in April
7 immediately preceding the beginning of the succeeding biennium.
8 (c) The Kentucky Board of Education shall not itself operate leased television
9 facilities, or undertake the preparation of the educational presentations or
10 films to be transmitted thereby, but may enter into one (1) or more contracts
11 to provide therefor, with any public agency and instrumentality of the
12 Commonwealth having, or able to provide, a staff with proper technical
13 qualifications, upon which agency and instrumentality the board, through the
14 chief state school officer and the Department of Education, is represented in
15 such manner as to coordinate matters of curriculum with the curricula
16 prescribed for the public schools of the Commonwealth. Any contract for the
17 operation of the leased television or related facilities may permit limited and
18 special uses of the television or related facilities for other programs in the
19 public interest, subject to the reasonable terms and conditions as the board and
20 the operating agency and instrumentality may agree upon; but any contract
21 shall affirmatively forbid the use of the television or related facilities, at any
22 time or in any manner, in the dissemination of political propaganda or in
23 furtherance of the interest of any political party or candidate for public office,
24 or for commercial advertising. No lease between the board and the State
25 Property and Buildings Commission shall bind the board to pay rentals for
26 more than one (1) fiscal biennium at a time, subject to the aforesaid renewal
27 options. The board may receive and may apply to rental payments under any
